memberdef.argsstring: (Schema schema, int specId, List< PartitionField > fields, int lastAssignedFieldId)
memberdef.name: PartitionSpec

detaileddescription.para: Returns the Schema for this spec.
Returns the ID of this spec.
Returns the list of partition fields for this spec.
Returns the field that partitions the given source field

parameterdescription.para: a field id from the source schema

simplesect.para: the field that partitions the given source field

detaileddescription.para: Returns a StructType for partition data defined by this spec.
Returns a struct matching partition information as written into manifest files. See {} for a struct with field ID's potentially re-assigned to avoid conflict.
Returns true if this spec is equivalent to the other, with partition field ids ignored. That is, if both specs have the same number of fields, field order, field name, source columns, and transforms.

simplesect.para: true if the specs have the same fields, source columns, and transforms.

detaileddescription.para: Returns the source field ids for identity partitions.

simplesect.para: a set of source ids for the identity partitions.

detaileddescription.para: Returns a spec for unpartitioned tables.

simplesect.para: a partition spec with no partitions

detaileddescription.para: Creates a new partition spec builder for the given Schema.

simplesect.para: a partition spec builder for the given schema

detaileddescription.para: Represents how to produce partition data for a table.
Partition data is produced by transforming columns in a table. Each column transform is represented by a named PartitionField.
